Main objective
  Students can define and identify game loops
  Use a while loop to simulate game play
  
Standards


In class exercises
  Use of while loop and proper conditions
  implementing an update() method that will update information (such as character position/movement)
  implementing a paintComponent() that will draw the screen with the updated information
  Creating a KeyHandler class to gather user key input
  
Notes
  Students will be following along with examples in class
  KeyEvent
  KeyListener
  Graphics
  2DGraphics
  
Resources
  source code for GamePanel and KeyHandler
  
  
Assignments
  Update their game so that user can move a rectangle around the game panel window
